{
  "texts": [
    "The sample includes models from Meta [22,23], Mistral AI [18], Google [14], Alibaba [28], DeepSeek [9,10], Microsoft [1], and OpenAI [26].",
    "Parameter counts range from 4 billion to 671 billion, and the sample includes both standard instruction-tuned models and reasoning-capable variants.Analysis was restricted to open-weight models to enable measuring parameter count and examining training variations, testing whether model size correlates with disclosure.",
    "This sample provides broad coverage of contemporary training methodologies.",
    "The training paradigm studied involves transformer-based pretraining with RLHF and safety tuning, which is common across contemporary LLMs.",
    "Generalization is discussed in Limitations (4.4)."
  ]
}